main.title: Modules
main.subtitle: In control panel all content is managed inside modules. They come in many types, from basic text and select boxes, to rich text fields and image pickers. Fields are grouped into templates and components and can be reused in a number of different ways.
main.content:
Common Settings

All mdoules share the following settings regardless of type:

  • Display – The field's label shown throughout the control panel
  • Handle – The field's variable name used in templates
  • Instructions – Help text shown to your authors
  • Required - Wheter or not the field is required

Text Modules

Fields that store strings of text, rich content, or both.

  • Text
  • Textarea
  • Rich Text Editor

Buttons & Controls

Fields that provide selectable options or buttons that can control logic.

  • Radio - Set of radio buttons
  • Range - Number range slider (e.g opacity slider)
  • Toggle - Boolean
  • Checkbox - Set of chekbox buttons

Numbers

Fields that store numbers

  • Number - Float or integer number

Structured

Fields that have complex data structures.

  • Replicator - Field which allowes you to create custom template which can be easily replicated by author (e.g sponsors)
